  "response": "A short story typically ranges from 1,000 to 7,500 words. However, these numbers can vary based on the specific publication or context. Some contests and magazines may have stricter word limits, with many considering stories under 5,000 words as short. Ultimately, the focus should be on telling a complete narrative in a concise manner, so the length can also depend on the story's needs.",
